<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tags/Tools on Create A Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/tools/</link><description>Recent content in Tags/Tools on Create A Van Life</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>© 2026 Create A Van Life</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/tags/tools/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Best Budget Build Tools for a First Van Conversion</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-of/budget-build-tools/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/best-of/budget-build-tools/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;You do not need a garage full of tools for a strong first build. You need a small set of reliable tools and a clear sequence.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="callout-shortcode"&gt;
 &lt;p class="callout-title"&gt;Quick Answer&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;div class="callout-body"&gt;Buy fewer tools but buy reliable core tools: drill/driver, jigsaw, rivnut tool, crimper, torque wrench, and safety gear.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re keeping this high-level—no wiring instructions here. For installs, follow manufacturer guidance or work with a qualified installer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tools You’ll Actually Use in a First Build</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The fastest way to overspend on a build is buying every tool recommended online.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Buy First
 &lt;div id="buy-first" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#buy-first" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill/driver combo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jigsaw + quality blades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Crimper + multimeter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PPE and measuring tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Borrow or Rent
 &lt;div id="borrow-or-rent" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#borrow-or-rent" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialty saws&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rare-use heavy tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Why This Matters
 &lt;div id="why-this-matters" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#why-this-matters" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tool quality affects safety and finish quality, but tool count does not.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>